										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><td><strong>Component</strong></td><td><strong>Detail/Parameter</strong></td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Aims of Test Project</strong></td><td>1. To successfully arrange and orchestrate the Portuguese carol, <strong>&#8220;Eu tive um sonho, sonhei a paz&#8221;</strong>for mixed choir, string orchestra, piano, and percussion. 2. To test the collaborative dynamic with the two music directors in a short-term project. 3. To gain experience seeing a composed/orchestrated piece performed by a live ensemble.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Collaborators</strong></td><td>Two school music teachers (Choral Director and String Program Director).</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Duration/Timeline</strong></td><td>Approximately <strong>two weeks</strong> from agreeing on the piece to performance. <strong>Performance Date:</strong> December 4th. <strong>Rehearsal:</strong> Full ensemble run-through on December 3rd and a final rehearsal on December 4th.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Form/Structure</strong></td><td><strong>Choral Arrangement:</strong> Unison/two-part, with an emphasis on simplicity due to the short rehearsal time. <strong>Solo/Variation:</strong> Tenors will sing Verse 1, with the full ensemble joining in subsequent verses. <strong>Instrumentation:</strong> Choir (65-85 singers), String Orchestra (25-30 players, mixed level), Piano, and non-pitched Percussion (e.g., chimes). </td></tr><tr><td><strong>Practicalities</strong></td><td><strong>Media/Software:</strong> Sibelius (for notation). <strong>Language Coaching:</strong> The choral director will initially rely on native Portuguese speakers in the choir for diction. <strong>Feedback Loop:</strong>Communication via email/Zoom for quick feedback and adjustments on the score.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Management &amp; Setup</strong></td><td><strong>My Role:</strong> Composer/Arranger, Orchestrator, and Documentarian. <strong>Teachers&#8217; Roles:</strong> Performers, Music Directors, and Consultants on playability/singability for their students. </td></tr></tbody></table></figure>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
